\begin_layout Section
Other comments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
1.
 The experimental set up section is missing key details such as the permeability
 of the core and details of the core holder construction.
 I cannot tell if the core is epoxied into the PEEK holder or if it is of
 the Hasseler sleeve type design.
 If there is an overburden pressure applied, please specify it.
 The interfacial tensions of all of the fluids should be mentioned for completen
ess.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Reply: more detail is added to the experimental section now.
 The bentheimer core was covered with epoxy but not glued into the core
 holder.
 Instead, the dried epoxy on the surface of the core was shaped with a threading
 machine so the epoxy-covered core could be placed into the core holder,
 as shown in Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Core-holder-design"

\end_inset

.
 A confining (overburden) pressure equal to the injection pressure was applied,
 which is equal to the back pressure (95 bar) plus the pressure drop in
 the core.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The interfacial tensions are also added to the paper, also in the following
 table.
